      "span_text": "H. leucospilota samples were harvested freshly from the Persian Gulf, around the coastal cities of Qeshm and Kharg Islands, Iran. Samples were washed out and cleaned with fresh distilled water to detach detritus and external particles and stored at −20 ∘ C until the next usage in agreement with food and agriculture of the United Nations scale method [CITATION_1] ."
